publisher=P.W.%20Elverum%20%26%20Sun%2C%20Ltd.
lyrics=The%20true%20state%20of%20all%20things%3A%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20keep%20on%20not%20dying%2C%20the%20sun%20keeps%20on%20rising.%0D%0AI%20remember%20my%20life%20as%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20just%20some%0D%0Adreams%20that%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20trust%2C%20burning%20off%2C%20layered%20thick%2C%0D%0Aa%20cargo%20that%20I%20haul%2C%20wounds%20and%20loves%20unresolved.%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20wake%20up%20with%20the%20sun%20in%20my%20eyes.%0D%0AThe%20present%20moment%20tries%0D%0Abut%20now%20I%E2%80%99m%20back%20where%20I%20was%20when%20I%20was%2020%2C%0D%0Acrashing%20through%20salal%20alone%20and%20mumbling%2C%0D%0Aone%20moment%20thinking%20I%E2%80%99m%20wise%0D%0Aand%20in%20the%20next%20one%20I%20writhe%2C%0D%0Atrying%20to%20re-remind%20myself%20of%20something%0D%0Alearned%20then%20forgotten.%20%20Countless%20sunrises%20%0D%0Aburying%20the%20things%20I%E2%80%99d%20figured%20out%20the%20day%20before.%0D%0ALike%20that%20I%20probably%20won%E2%80%99t%20find%20shelter%20%0D%0Ain%20the%20arms%20of%20any%20other%20person%0D%0Athough%20I%20will%20try.%0D%0AAgain%20I%E2%80%99ll%20deny%0D%0Athe%20blanketing%20sky%2C%0D%0Athe%20thing%20I%20just%20realized%0D%0Afor%20probably%20the%20millionth%20time%2C%0D%0Athat%20walking%20with%20my%20knees%20trembling%20is%0D%0Athe%20true%20state%20of%20all%20things.%0D%0A%0D%0AThe%20true%20state%20of%20all%20things%20is%20a%20waterfall%0D%0Awith%20no%20bottom%20crashing%20end%20%0D%0Aand%20no%20ledge%20to%20plummet%20off%0D%0Afull%20of%20debris%20and%20flowers%2C%20%0D%0Anever%20not%20falling%2C%0D%0Aand%20in%20it%20we%20swim%20and%20fall.%0D%0ASometimes%20beside%2C%20often%20apart.%0D%0AIt%E2%80%99s%20just%20chaos%20heaving.%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20wake%20up%20with%20the%20sun%20in%20my%20eyes%0D%0Abeneath%20present%20moment%20skies%2C%0D%0Asquinting%20and%20wondering%20how%20I%20got%20here.%0D%0AGoing%20through%20the%20contents%20of%20my%20backpack%2C%0D%0Ashaking%20out%20the%20dust%20to%20bring%20some%20empty%20space%20back%2C%0D%0Afilling%20a%20long%20merch%20table%20with%20artifacts%2C%20%0D%0Alooking%20back%20to%20see%20if%20I%20could%20draw%20a%20map%0D%0Athat%20leads%20to%20now.%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20remember%20where%20I%20was%0D%0Awhen%20I%20was%2020%20or%2017%20or%2023.%0D%0AThe%20disinterested%20sun%20would%20still%20rise%20every%20morning%0D%0Asame%20as%20now.%20%20Dawn%20was%20loud.%0D%0AI%20took%20my%20breakfast%20to%20the%20couch%20on%20the%20porch%20of%20the%20punk%20house.%0D%0ACoffee%20and%20low%20tide%20smell%20and%20my%20life%20stretching%20out.%0D%0ASpending%20hours%20each%20morning%20reading%20poems%20and%20staring%20off%20%0D%0Aand%20then%20snapping%20back%20to%20urgency%2C%20I%20did%20my%20dishes%0D%0Athen%20I%20would%20sprint%20to%20the%20studio%20again.%0D%0ASpend%20all%20day%20and%20night%20digging%20in%2C%20%0D%0Adistorted%20bass%2C%20spliced%20tape%2C%20singing%20lines%20like%20%0D%0A%E2%80%9Cthere%E2%80%99s%20no%20end%E2%80%9D%20%0D%0Aand%20%E2%80%9CI%20won%E2%80%99t%20look%20for%20you%20in%20my%20room%E2%80%9D%20about%20my%20friends.%0D%0AI%20checked%20themicrophones%40hotmail.com%20like%20once%20a%20week.%0D%0AI%20would%20drive%20out%20to%20the%20ocean%20and%20not%20tell%20anybody.%0D%0AI%20watched%20Crouching%20Tiger%2C%20Hidden%20Dragon%20in%20a%20dollar%20theater%20in%20Aberdeen.%0D%0AIt%20was%20a%20rainy%20matinee%202001%2C%20Sunday%2C%20March%2018th%2C%20%0D%0Aand%20in%20the%20parking%20lot%20afterward%0D%0Afor%20a%20few%20minutes%20in%20the%20rain%0D%0AI%20stood%20glowing%20with%20ideas%20of%20what%20I%20might%20try%20to%20convey%0D%0Awith%20this%20music.%20%20At%20that%20moment%20my%20mind%20flashing%20like%20a%20blade.%0D%0AA%2022-year-old%20in%20flip%20flops%20running%20around%20in%20an%20empty%20mall%20parking%20lot%20lost%20in%20a%20martial%20arts%20fantasy%2C%20%0D%0Ait%20looks%20ridiculous%20now%20but%20the%20truth%20is%3A%0D%0Aalone%20there%0D%0Asomething%20was%20formed.%0D%0AThe%20way%20they%20held%20themselves%20upright%20with%20tea%20in%20the%20opening%20scenes%2C%0D%0Aa%20warm%20formality%2C%20spines%20straight%20and%20feet%20planted%20wide%2C%0D%0Aun-tip-over-able%20like%20the%20bamboo%E2%80%99d%20undulating%20hills%2C%0D%0Awalking%20slowly%2C%20making%20eye%20contact%2C%20gliding%2C%0D%0Athe%20sound%20of%20empty%20wind%20when%20they%20sword-fought%20weightless%20in%20the%20bamboo%0D%0Awith%20a%20purity%20of%20heart%20that%20transcends%20gravity%0D%0Aleaping%20off%20the%20mountain%20into%20ambiguity%0D%0Afalling%20slow%0D%0Aas%20the%20end%20credits%20rolled.%0D%0AI%20decided%20I%20would%20try%20to%20make%20music%20that%20contained%20this%20deeper%20peace%0D%0Aburied%20underneath%20distorted%20bass%2C%20fog%20imbued%20with%20light%20and%20emptiness%2C%0D%0AI%20kept%20on%20driving%20out%20to%20the%20ocean.%0D%0AIt%20was%20raining%20so%20hard%2C%20I%20was%20wet%20wool%20caked%20with%20sand.%0D%0AI%20watched%20the%20dunes%20migrate%20slowly.%0D%0A%0D%0ALost%20mind%20in%20the%20tall%20grass%0D%0ASlowly%20the%20sound%20of%20roaring%20waves%20returned.%20%20I%20rose.%20%20%0D%0AI%20returned%20to%20my%20station%20wagon%20with%20a%20wet%20face.%0D%0AExtravagant%20solitude%20invigorates.%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20drove%20back%20to%20Olympia%20clear%20headed%20temporarily%20and%20went%20back%20into%20the%20studio%20to%20resume%20whatever%20this%20thing%20is%3A%20%20%0D%0Athis%20spooling%20out%20repetitive%20decades-long%20song%20string%2C%20%0D%0Athis%20river%20coursing%20through%20my%20life%2C%20%0D%0Athese%20wild%20swipes%20at%20meaning.%0D%0A%0D%0ANow%20I%20circle%20back%20to%20look%20into%20the%20spring.%0D%0AWhen%20I%20was%2017%20it%20was%201995.%20%20%0D%0AI%20put%20the%20name%20%E2%80%9CMicrophones%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20tapes%20I%20would%20make%20late%20at%20night%20after%20work%20at%20the%20record%20store.%20%20I%20was%20already%20by%20then%20a%20couple%20years%20deep%20into%20this%20weird%20pursuit%20playing%20drums%2C%20copying%20lyrics%20out%20to%20hang%20them%20in%20my%20room%20until%20I%20started%20making%20my%20own%20embarrassing%20early%20tries%20at%20this%20thing%20that%20sings%20at%20night%20above%20the%20house%2C%20%0D%0Abranches%20in%20the%20wind%20bending%20wordlessly.%20%20%0D%0AI%20wanted%20to%20capture%20it%20on%20tape.%0D%0AAt%20first%20I%20called%20my%20recordings%20a%20different%20name.%20%20I%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Microphones%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%203rd%20cassette%20I%20made.%20%20%0D%0AI%20loved%20recording%20and%20the%20equipment%20seemed%20to%20be%20living%20and%20it%20sang%20to%20me%20like%20static%20interference%20from%20the%20small%20AM%20radio%20station%20down%20the%20street%2C%20night%20in%20Anacortes%20in%20the%20mid%2090%E2%80%99s%2C%20oil%20tankers%20rumbling.%20%20%0D%0AI%20stayed%20late%20recording%20every%20night%20then%20I%20drove%20back%20to%20my%20parents%E2%80%99%20house.%20%20My%20headlights%20through%20the%20trees%20along%20Heart%20Lake%20Road%2C%0D%0Awinding%20down%20the%20dark%20slope%20beneath%20Mount%20Erie%2C%20I%20was%20already%20who%20I%20am%3A%20%0D%0A%20a%20bottle%20of%20india%20ink%2C%20masking%20tape%2C%20a%20cardboard%20box%20of%20dubbed%20cassettes%2C%20Julie%20Doiron%2C%20Tori%20Amos%2C%20Cranberries%2C%20Sinead%20O%E2%80%99Connor%2C%20Eric%E2%80%99s%20Trip%2C%20Red%20House%20Painters%2C%20Sonic%20Youth%2C%20This%20Mortal%20Coil%2C%20My%20Bloody%20Valentine%2C%20Jack%20Kerouac%2C%20radio%20stations%20coming%20from%20Canada%2C%20Elevator%20To%20Hell%2C%20Moonsocket%2C%20Gravel%2C%20Lou%20Barlow%2C%20the%20first%20mysterious%20Palace%20record%2C%20Glenn%20Branca%2C%20Beat%20Happening%2C%20Jale%2C%20Snailhouse%2C%20Pond%2C%20Steven%20Jesse%20Bernstein%2C%20%20Loren%20Mazzacane%20Connors%2C%20Lee%20Ranaldo%2C%20Julie%20Doucet%2C%20Chester%20Brown%2C%20Krzysztof%20Kieslowski%2C%20dubbed%20VHS%20tapes%2C%20the%20scenes%20in%20the%20Black%20Lodge%2C%20%0D%0AKurt%20Cobain%20had%20died.%20%20I%20had%20my%20driver%E2%80%99s%20license%20and%20a%20girlfriend%20and%20we%E2%80%99d%20cling%20to%20each%20other%20and%20dream%20that%20anything%E2%80%99s%20permanent.%0D%0A%0D%0AEven%20back%20then%20the%20beast%20of%20uninvited%20change%20insisted%20itself%20in%2C%20and%20look%20here%20it%20still%20hangs%20%0D%0Abut%20when%20I%20was%20young%20I%E2%80%99d%20go%20driving%20in%20the%20rain.%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20saw%20Stereolab%20in%20Bellingham%20and%20they%20played%20one%20chord%20for%20fifteen%20minutes.%20%20Something%20in%20me%20shifted.%20%20I%20brought%20back%20home%20belief%20I%20could%20create%20eternity.%20%20%0D%0ALeaning%20the%20guitar%20up%20on%20the%20amp%2C%20taping%20down%20organ%20keys%2C%20feeding%20back%20forever%2C%20distorted%20waves%20of%20cymbals%20oceany.%20%20%20%20%0D%0ASlowly%20starting%20to%20try%20to%20move%20the%20words%20beyond%20mere%20melancholy%20into%20something%20that%20rings%20true%20and%20old%20and%20useful%20hopefully%2C%20but%20when%20I%20was%2017%20I%20sang%20in%20the%20moment%20hurt%20romantically%2C%20grasping%20in%20the%20dark%2C%20like%0D%0A%E2%80%9Cshadows%20of%20the%20moon%20%0D%0Aon%20the%20back%20%0D%0Aof%20the%20car%20seat%20%0D%0Awhere%20she%20sat%20once.%E2%80%9D%20%0D%0AIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20bad%20but%20I%20know%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20deeper%2C%20beneath%20pain%2C%20beneath%20the%20human.%0D%0A%0D%0AIs%20it%20because%20my%20parents%20barely%20had%20any%20money%20and%20preferred%20to%20leave%20the%20baby%20in%20the%20garden%20that%20I%20grew%20up%20to%20blur%20the%20boundary%20between%20myself%20and%20the%20actual%20churning%20dirt%20of%20this%20place%2C%20that%20it%20feels%20normal%20to%20me%20to%20speak%20with%20the%20voice%20of%20weather%2C%20to%20build%20and%20move%20into%20a%20mirage%20made%20of%20songs%20cascading%20down%20a%20rock%20face%20in%20a%20homemade%20myth%3F%0D%0A%0D%0AEven%20deeper%20back%20into%20the%20mist%3A%0D%0Awhen%20I%20was%2012%20or%2013%20on%20a%20family%20trip%20we%20hiked%20down%20a%20steep%20bluff%20to%20an%20ocean%20beach%20in%20whipping%20rain.%20%20My%20little%20brother%E2%80%99s%20clothes%20got%20wet%20from%20playing%20in%20the%20winter%20waves.%20%20My%20parents%20made%20a%20fire%20of%20smoky%20driftwood%20and%20we%20huddled%20in%20and%20took%20his%20wet%20clothes%20off%20and%20held%20him%20naked%20above%20the%20flames.%20%20Smelling%20like%20smoke%20and%20salt%20on%20the%20drive%20home%2C%20surely%20this%20experience%20explains%20something%20about%20whoever%20it%20was%20that%20sang%20all%20these%20songs.%0D%0A%0D%0AWhen%20you%E2%80%99re%20younger%20every%20single%20thing%20vibrates%20with%20significance.%20%20%0D%0AGazing%20at%20the%20details%20in%20the%20artwork%20of%20a%207%E2%80%9D%2C%20devouring%20every%20word%20in%20a%20zine%2C%20there%20was%20barely%20internet.%0D%0AMeaning%20gets%20attributed%20wherever%20appetite%20bestows%20a%20thing%20with%20resonating%20glowing%20ringing%20out%20through%20a%20life.%0D%0AWhat%20from%20these%20times%20do%20I%20carry%20with%20me%20still%3F%20%20The%20things%20I%20survive%20return%20repeatedly%20and%20I%20find%20again%20that%20I%20am%20a%20newborn%20every%20time.%0D%0A%0D%0AWhen%20I%20wake%20alone%20in%20the%20dark%20again%0D%0AI%20swim%0D%0Aout%20into%20the%20lake%20of%20the%20heart%0D%0Aand%20in.%0D%0A%0D%0AWhen%20I%20got%20back%20to%20Olympia%20from%20the%20ocean%0D%0AI%20woke%20up%20early%20before%20dawn%20to%20start%20recording.%0D%0AThe%20things%20I%20wanted%20to%20communicate%20had%20to%20do%20with%20finding%20how%20to%20break%20out%20from%20seeing%20only%20the%20inside%20of%20reflected%20ocean%20on%20the%20sky.%0D%0AIt%20was%20early%202001%20and%20I%20was%20almost%2023.%20%20I%E2%80%99d%20finished%20recording%20the%20Glow%20pt.%202%20and%20I%20was%20either%20always%20on%20tour%20or%20setting%20up%20a%20tour%2C%20always%20running%2C%20voracious%2C%20thirsty.%20%0D%0AI%E2%80%99d%20go%20out%20to%20the%20lake%20with%20friends%2C%20swim%20out%20to%20the%20middle%20and%20dive%20as%20far%20as%20I%20could%20down%20to%20where%20the%20water%20gets%20cold%2C%20with%20open%20eyes.%0D%0AWe%E2%80%99d%20go%20up%20on%20the%20roof%20at%20night%20and%20actually%20contemplate%20the%20moon.%20%20My%20friends%20and%20I%20trying%20to%20blow%20each%20others%E2%80%99%20minds%20just%20lying%20there%20gazing%2C%20young%20and%20ridiculous%20and%20we%20meant%20it%2C%20our%20eyes%20watering.%0D%0AThe%20moon%20without%20abstraction%20then%20became%20a%20floating%20ball%20of%20rock%20in%20outer%20space%2C%20not%20a%20sticker%20or%20a%20light%20or%20a%20hole%20through%20black%20paper.%20%20We%20were%20making%20food%20and%20records%20and%20paintings%20and%20walking%20around%20beneath%20a%20real%20infinity.%20%20I%20felt%20my%20size.%0D%0AThat%20brief%20dissipating%20shock%20of%20looking%20into%20outer%20space%20and%20seeing%20just%20for%20a%20second%20the%20bottomless%20distance%20pressed%20against%20my%20face.%20%20My%20little%20mind%20trying%20to%20write%20it%20down%2C%20zooming%20out%2C%20a%20faint%20yelp%20lost%20in%20a%20thunderstorm.%20%20Sufficiently%20small%2C%20thinking%20on%20the%20geologic%20scale%2C%20making%20the%20voice%20of%20mountains.%0D%0AReaching%20beyond%20my%20old%20concerns%20from%20when%20I%20was%2017%20in%201995.%20%20All%20the%20layers%20of%20life%20glint%20in%20my%20flashing%20eye%0D%0Asimultaneously%20and%20at%20any%20moment%20we%20could%20die%20%0D%0Aand%20so%20with%20urgency%20I%20keep%20a%20candle%20by%20my%20side%0D%0Aand%20watch%20it%20disappear%20and%20glow%20at%20the%20same%20time.%0D%0AThe%20weather%20moves%20across%20the%20land%20and%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20reason.%20%20This%20rippling%20uncertainty%20beneath%20our%20bones%20is%20still%20the%20true%20state%20of%20all%20things.%0D%0AIt%20was%20at%20a%20truck%20stop%20in%20northern%20Italy.%20%20I%20was%20on%20tour%20playing%20drums%20and%20always%20wandering%20off%20alone%20squinting%20into%20the%20setting%20sun%2C%20my%20notebook%20filling.%0D%0AI%20was%20touring%2C%20living%20on%20an%20alternate%20plane%20within%20but%20set%20apart%20from%20this%20life%20where%20people%20wake%20and%20work%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20self-uproot%20each%20day.%20%20Instead%20we%20passed%20through%20the%20towns%20like%20criminals.%20%20I%20was%20so%20gladly%20included%20in%20this%20rare%20world%2C%20this%20moving%20cult%20of%20groundlessness%2C%20roomless%2C%20moving%2C%20awake.%0D%0AAcross%20that%20parking%20lot%2C%20recognition%20of%20the%20same%3A%20%20Another%20touring%20American%20band%2C%20Bonnie%20%E2%80%98Prince%E2%80%99%20Billy%2C%20all%20dressed%20in%20matching%20track%20suits%20and%20sunglasses%2C%20grizzled%20and%20silly%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20Italian%20tour%20costume%2C%20blending%20in%20but%20not%20really%2C%20and%20their%20playfulness%20with%20persona%20liberated%20me%20with%20permeability.%20%20I%20thought%20%0D%0A%E2%80%9Cwho%20is%20it%20even%20that%20sings%20and%20who%20comes%20to%20life%20between%20the%20ears%20of%20the%20hearers%20in%20the%20rooms%20at%20night%20and%20how%20can%20we%20all%20get%20deep%3F%E2%80%9D%0D%0AThe%20packaging%20distracts%20from%20the%20nourishment%20it%20wraps.%20%20Fixation%20on%20the%20singer%E2%80%99s%20face%20or%20on%20the%20band%E2%80%99s%20name%20keeps%20us%20groveling%20and%20blind%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20a%20sea%2C%20unsubmerged%20in%20the%20singing%20waterfall%2C%20looking%20for%20a%20door%20into%20the%20mansion%2C%20taking%20this%20weird%20art%20project%20out%20into%20public%2C%20indulging%20in%20cultivated%20ambiguity%20about%20participants%E2%80%99%20identities%2C%20letting%20misperceptions%20hang%20because%20nothing%E2%80%99s%20really%20true.%0D%0AWith%20this%20imagined%20collective%20called%20the%20Microphones%20I%20wrote%20about%20climbing%20up%20and%20dying%20and%20flying%20off%20as%20vultures%2C%20and%20a%20universe%20beyond%2C%20innocent%20of%20the%20real%20air%20of%20death%20that%20awaited%20down%20the%20path.%0D%0AAt%20the%20very%20end%20of%202002%20I%20took%20the%20Microphones%20name%20and%20crumpled%20it%20up%20and%20burned%20it%20in%20a%20cave%20on%20the%20frozen%20edge%20of%20Northern%20Norway.%20%20%0D%0AI%20made%20a%20boundary%20between%20two%20eras%20of%20my%20life%2C%20a%20feeble%20gesture%20at%20making%20chaos%20seem%20organized.%0D%0AThe%20roaring%20river%20carves%20on%2C%20laughing%20at%20my%20efforts%20%0D%0Awhile%20the%20idea%20of%20something%20called%20%E2%80%9CMount%20Eerie%E2%80%9D%20engulfed%20me%20and%20time%20refuses%20to%20stop.%0D%0AMany%20many%20years%20later%20I%20heard%20%E2%80%9CFreezing%20Moon%E2%80%9D%20by%20Mayhem%20and%20these%20words%20jumped%20out%3A%20%0D%0A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20cemetery%20lights%20up%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9Ceternity%20opens%E2%80%9D%0D%0Aand%20I%20say%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20stays%20the%20same%2C%20no%20one%20knows%20anything%E2%80%9D.%20%20Someone%20else%20lives%20in%20the%20house%20I%20used%20to%20live%20in%20and%20soon%20it%20will%20be%20torn%20down%20or%20burn%20and%20who%20would%20even%20want%20to%20live%20in%20a%20prolonged%20stagnation%3F%20%20I%20am%20older%20now%20and%20I%20no%20longer%20feel%20the%20same%20way%20that%20I%20did%20even%20five%20seconds%20ago.%20%20%0D%0AWatch%20me%20thrash%20around%20and%20try%20to%20gracefully%20allow%20the%20past%20to%20hang%20like%20%E2%80%9Cno%20big%20deal.%E2%80%9D%0D%0ABands%20that%20break%20up%20and%20then%20reunite%20for%20money%20can%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20but%20it%20makes%20me%20glad%20that%20I%20am%20only%20this%20one%20contrary%20grump%20impossible%20to%20reunite.%20%20%0D%0ALive%2C%20the%20present%20moment%20burns.%0D%0AI%20will%20never%20stop%20singing%20this%20song.%20%20It%20goes%20on%20forever.%20%0D%0AI%20started%20when%20I%20was%20a%20kid%20and%20I%20still%20want%20to%20hold%20it%20lightly%3A%20%20this%20luxurious%20privilege%20to%20sit%20around%20frowning%20and%20wondering%20what%20it%20means%2C%20playing%20with%20words%20and%20trying%20to%20prove%20that%20names%20mean%20nothing.%0D%0AA%20finger%20pointed%20at%20the%20moon%20%0D%0A%20%20%20%20mistaken%20for%20something%20shining%20and%20true.%0D%0AI%20never%20used%20to%20think%20I%E2%80%99d%20still%20be%20sitting%20here%20at%2041%20trying%20to%20breathe%20calmly%20through%20the%20waves%20%0D%0Abut%20nothing%E2%80%99s%20really%20changed%20in%20this%20effort%20that%20never%20ends.%0D%0AWhen%20I%20took%20my%20shirt%20off%20in%20the%20yard%20I%20meant%20it%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20off.%20%20I%E2%80%99m%20still%20standing%20in%20the%20weather%20looking%20for%20meaning%20in%20the%20giant%20meaningless%20days%20of%20love%20and%20loss%20repeatedly%20waterfalling%20down%20and%20the%20sun%20relentlessly%20rises%20still.%20%20%0D%0AIt%20seems%20like%20I%E2%80%99ll%20never%20not%20lose%20wisdom.%20%20Constantly%20re-learning%20all%20the%20basics%2C%20never%20recognizing%20any%20faces%2C%20crawling%20out%20from%20under%20living%20layers%2C%20squinting%20in%20the%20light%20of%20earth%2C%20bathing%2C%20shaking%20off%20the%20weight%20of%20expectation%2C%20plus%20all%20this%20nostalgia%20is%20embarrassing%20so%20I%20walk%20into%20an%20unknown%20room%20without%20a%20name.%0D%0ASo%20what%20if%20I%20label%20this%20song%20%E2%80%9CMicrophones%20in%202020%E2%80%9D%3F%0D%0AI%20hope%20the%20absurdity%20that%20permeates%20everything%20joyfully%20rushes%20out%20and%20floods%20the%20room%20like%20water%20from%20the%20ceiling%2C%20undermining%20all%20of%20our%20delicate%20stabilities%2C%20admitting%20that%20each%20moment%20is%20a%20new%20collapsing%20building.%0D%0ANothing%20is%20true%20but%20this%20trembling%2C%20laughing%20in%20the%20wind.%0D%0AAnyway%20every%20song%20I%E2%80%99ve%20ever%20sung%20is%20about%20the%20same%20thing%3A%0D%0Astanding%20on%20the%20ground%20looking%20around%2C%20basically.%0D%0AIf%20there%20have%20to%20be%20words%2C%20they%20could%20just%20be%0D%0A%E2%80%9Cnow%20only%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthere%E2%80%99s%20no%20end%E2%80%9D
